<!--TAGS IN HTML NOTES-->
1.<html></html> - main html tag
2.<p></p>- paragraph tag
3.<title></title>- title tag
4.<body></body>- body tag
5.Use <!-- commenting out syntax--> click control+slash for commenting out after seleting the text
6.<h1></h1>,<h2></h2>.....<h6></h6>... differs in size and importance
7.<a href="...">display</a>- anchor tag - that add links to the page  , to add the link from same folder syntax: <a href="/web link">okay</a>
 <a href="..." targer="_main"></a>
8.<br />- breaks the line or newline
9.<img src="image address" alt="Random IMage"> - inserts image to the webpage, --> src=souce , alt= gives the alternate name when image doesnt get loaded 
10. link used directly from browser is "Absolute url"
11.Links used from same folder is "Relative url" , which is used with a slash "/".
12. <b></b>, <i></i> ,<u></u>u> - bold , italic , underline
13.<big></big> - big text , <small>for small text</small>
14. <hr> - horizontal ruler - inserts a line between two lines
15.<sub></sub> - subscript
16. we use <pre></pre> tag if we want to count spaces and newline in paragraph instead of paragraph.

*****************************************************************
SEMANTIC TAGS                            NON SEMANTIC TAGS
whose name cleary mentions its use ,     Name is not related to the tag's usage
p , a ,                                  <div>Occupies the space of whole line</div> , <span>Occupies only required space</span>
                                         block tags                                     inlne tags
BEtter to use semantic than using non semantic one
*****************************************************************
17.<header></header> and <footer></footer> for header and footer
18.It is advisable to create sections in main using <main></main> and <section></section> tags 
19.<aside></aside> that seo doesnt read , used for the text that is not the part of main section. 
20.<article></article> for inserting <article></article>
21. Target="_main" , in <a href> used to open the link in next tab keeping the previous one intact.
22. Click the image , <a href="link"><img src="link of image">
23.div tag - it is a comtainer for other html elements , it is a block element that occpies whole width of line 
NOTE : when more elements are to be changed(like bg colour) in the same manner we use div tag
24. span tag - where only required space is used 
25. To display the data in the form of lists ....................... 
        Unordered                |              Ordered
        In the form of books                    In the form of numbers
        <ul> </ul>                              <ol></ol>
        <li></li> list element                   <li>list element</li>

26. TABLES IN <HTML></HTML> 
    <table>table tag , table creation starts from here</table>
    <caption>caption , info about the table content</caption>
    <th>table header tag</th> , <th colspan="number of columns having common header name"></th>
    <tr>table row tag</tr>
    <td>table data tag</td>
    <thead>table head</thead>
    <tbody>table body</tbody>
27. FORMS IN <HTML></HTML>
    <form action="file name collecting the data">collects the data from user </form>

    FORM ELEMENTS:
    <INPUT TYPE="text" placeholder="Username"></INPUT>
    <input type="password" placeholder="Password"></input>
